ditionally regarded as the founder of the Christian Church. The name derives, via Latin, from Greek <i>petros</i> ‘stone, rock’. This is used as a translation of the Aramaic byname <i>Cephas</i>, given to the apostle  Simon  son of Jona, to distinguish him from another of the same name (  Simon Zelotes ). ‘When Jesus beheld him, he said, Thou art Simon the son of Jona: thou shalt be called Cephas, which is by interpretation, A stone’ (John 1:42). According to Matthew 16:17–18, Christ says more explicitly, ‘Blessed art thou, Simon Bar-jona … thou art Peter, and upon this rock I will build my church’. The name has been in continuous use since the Middle Ages."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1702076,"age":66,"year":"1436","julianDay":2245548,"title":"The Engelbrekt Rebellion","description":"Engelbrekt Engelbrektsson, a Swedish mine owner and statesman, led a rebellion against Eric of Pomerania, King of the Kalmar Union. Sweden was upset with the Danes' interference with Swedish exports and unjust collection of taxes. The Engelbrekt Rebellion led to the deposing of Eric of Pomerania and the eventual dissolution of the Kalmar Union.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Ragvald Petersson Gumsehuvud was born about 1370, in Gotland, Sweden. He had at least 1 son with Ragnhild Johansdotter. He died in 1452, in Västra Götaland, Sweden, at the age of 83."},"et":{"Abt. 1370–1452":"umbes 1370–1452","1380–1460":"1380–1460","1405–1463":"1405–1463","1370–1452":"1370–1452","1436":"1436","Abt. 1405":"1405","1452":"1452","1463":"1463","1460":"1460","1370":"1370","1380":"1380","Abt. 1370":"umbes 1370","1405":"1405","Sweden":"Rootsi","Västra Götaland, Sverige":"Västra Götaland, Rootsi","Västra Götland, Sverige":"Gotland, Rootsi"},"fi":{"Abt. 1370–1452":"noin 1370–1452","1380–1460":"1380–1460","1405–1463":"1405–1463","1370–1452":"1370–1452","1436":"1436","Abt. 1405":"1405","1452":"1452","1463":"1463","1460":"1460","1370":"1370","1380":"1380","Abt. 1370":"noin 1370","1405":"1405","Sweden